        "title": "fix: scope chart selection band to bar width and remove cost item detail lines",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- shrink chart selection band from midpoint-to-midpoint to bar width: use calendar-day slot width so the grey highlight sits under the bar regardless of gaps in the data\r\n- keep selection on the last hovered bar when cursor is between bars ŌĆö no longer jumps to nearest at the midpoint\r\n- apply same fix to `CostHistoryChartMenuView`, `CreditsHistoryChartMenuView`, and `UsageBreakdownChartMenuView`; `PlanUtilizationHistoryChartMenuView` uses `Layout.barWidth / 2` since bars are fixed-width\r\n- remove \"Today\" and \"Last 30 days\" detail lines from the Cost menu item; cost info remains available in the tooltip on hover\r\n\r\n## Tests\r\n\r\n- update `StatusMenuCostMenuCardTests` to assert new behavior: `costMenuVisibleDetailLines` returns `[]` and fallback attributed title is plain \"Cost\"\r\n- full suite passed 488 tests, 0 failures\r\n- `make check` passed; SwiftFormat clean, SwiftLint 0 violations\r\n\r\n## Verification\r\n\r\n- built and ran locally; selection band visually confirmed to sit under bar body\r\n- band renders identically for all bars including first/last and bars with large data gaps\r\n- Cost menu item shows \"Cost\" with submenu arrow only ŌĆö no detail lines\r\n\r\n## Screenshots\r\n\r\nBefore:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"625\" height=\"775\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-19 at 5 57 26ŌĆ»PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d4441b6b-d6f4-4dd7-85c8-617b1cabf0ea\" />\r\n\r\nAfter:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"621\" height=\"742\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-19 at 5 56 43ŌĆ»PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/089c857d-a71d-407e-ba59-83d3d260c7b6\" />\r\n",
